onion
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:1. a wild variety of onion with masses of attractive white flowers. 2. for various plants: see also Maori onion; ONION PLANT, FLOWER, WEED; GRASS; a local weed also called (WILD) GARLIC q.v. 1. NATIVE ONION (see also MAORI ONION) cit. at Native Leek. See Leek. 2. WILD ONION spp.  -->[AND =onion weed 1864, 1901 Bulbinera sp] WILD GARLIC, =CROW GARLIC =ONION FLOWER,=ONION WEED etc.
